To compile link make.inc to the appropriate file for your compiler.
Be sure correct modules are loaded. Example helper scripts 
(make_k.sh make_pfe.sh) do this for the k and pleiades clusters.

Recommend using Intel MKL libraries, but can also download and compile lapack as follows:
wget https://github.com/Reference-LAPACK/lapack/archive/refs/tags/v3.12.1.tar.gz
tar -xvf v3.12.1.tar.gz
cd lapack-3.12.1
cp make.inc.example make.inc
make

Then add 
LDFLAGS = /your/path/here/liblapack.a /your/path/here/librefblas.a
to your make.inc


For the modeshape NASTRAN conversion helpers opt_to_txt.py and plot_modes.py:
Requirements
------------
  - Python 3.9 or later (tested with 3.13 on mac)

1. Create a virtual environment (recommended)
----------------------------------------------

  macOS / Linux:
    python3 -m venv venv
    source venv/bin/activate

  Windows:
    python3 -m venv venv
    venv\Scripts\activate


2. Install dependencies
-----------------------

  Install everything at once:

    pip install numpy pyNastran pyvista "imageio[ffmpeg]"

  Or install individually:

    pip install numpy              # Core (required for both scripts)
    pip install pyNastran          # OP2 extraction (required for op2_to_txt.py)
    pip install pyvista            # Visualization (required for plot_modes.py)
    pip install "imageio[ffmpeg]"  # MP4 export (optional, for --save-anim)


3. Make scripts executable (macOS / Linux)
------------------------------------------

    chmod +x op2_to_txt.py plot_modes.py


4. Verify installation
----------------------

    op2_to_txt.py --help
    plot_modes.py --help
